<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-13T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-13T07:00:00-05:00" n="1247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1247">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68119/11–1345: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-13T14:00:00+02:00">November
                                    13, 1945—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1450. My 1445, November 12, 4 p.m. In conversation with Prime Minister he
                            asked whether I was satisfied with form of interim reply <pb facs="1290" n="1278" xml:id="pg_1278"/> given me by Erkin to our proposal for
                            revision Montreux Convention or whether I would prefer a written reply.
                            I said that Erkin had explained that his statement should be regarded as
                            official interim reply of Turkish Govt pending receipt of views of
                            British and Soviet Govts when a more detailed and presumably written
                            reply would be made. Under these circumstances I said that I personally
                            saw no reason to request any change in form of this interim reply.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>